U.S.: Recurring is the mother of wisdom
It is comic that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, to whom he himself took for the stupidest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, eagerly awaited, it was demonstrated that it was a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the speech "like in Iraq" used several times, but it also failed to use the title of the January 2007 Bush Declaration for its own statement: "A new way forward".
It was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from the civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision and with catastrophic consequences".
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that nothing is being said about Iraq in the news today.
Bush's reputation did not improve, but objectively left his successor a much more favorable initial situation than was expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama expects the miracle to be repeated.
The camp captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander in charge of the Afghan General Stanley McCristal operation. He, even in spite of the traditional subordinated relations, subjected the indecisive gunmen in the White House to severe criticism.
He asked 40,000 men to improve the situation.
The president was vacant for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so he cheated at least on the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he had previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's entire strategy seems to be its goal, to start withdrawing the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and ending this procedure in three years.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well-organized, and its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: it is not possible to trust anyone and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing the boss every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After him will remain the patriarchal tribal relations.
To balance the interests of different ethnic groups is extremely complicated due to confused relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the whole operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocked by its volunteerism.
During the last eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to deteriorate and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to war to "come home soon", will perform some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsibility, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of US defeat.
NATO's last summit showed that Europeans are increasingly less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and increased sanctions do not have any effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphal withdrawal of the troops of Afghanistan.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic reversal for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is that three years are missing for the presidential elections and therefore there is still much time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
